{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":49340,"duration_api_ms":35700,"num_turns":3,"result":"All 1169 tests pass (357 lib + 128 integration + 1 doc + 683 unit), clippy clean. The flaky checkpoint test didn't fire this time.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Fixed three lineage edge cases: (1) safe_plan_hash_backfill now handles 'start before plan, complete after plan' — when snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation and plan_hash are both None and the entry is still Running, both are populated from the current snapshot since no prior plan existed to conflict with; terminal entries remain untouched. (2) Duplicate-row repair in record_task_run_start now pre-merges the canonical (collapsed) entry into the raw row before backfill, so that in duplicate-row states the most complete metadata from all duplicates is preserved rather than potentially picking the stale first raw row. (3) merge_attempt_entries now merges snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation from the secondary entry when the primary's is None, preventing duplicate cleanup from permanently dropping the only provenance-bearing copy.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\",\n    \"Pre-existing flaky checkpoint test (worktree_adapter_excludes_runtime_workspace_from_checkpoint_commits) intermittently fails due to environment issues — unrelated to these changes.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation merge to merge_attempt_entries in model.rs:325-328: when the primary entry's snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation is None, it is now filled from the secondary entry, matching the existing pattern for plan_hash, run_id, and outcome_detail\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated safe_plan_hash_backfill in fs.rs:2628-2669 to handle the 